The paper discusses the use of syntactic parsing in natural language processing, specifically in sentiment analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also evaluates the performance of different parsing algorithms, which falls under the scope of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of state-of-the-art algorithms and the focus on computational efficiency suggests a possible fit with cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
